<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 6:01PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Rutherford and northwestern Cleveland Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 601 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles south of Morganton, or 5 miles west of Casar, moving northeast
at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Casar and Polkville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
